# 🗣️ Bezaleel - Voice Digital Assistant

![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/Python-3776AB?style=for-the-badge&logo=python&logoColor=white)
![Jupyter](https://img.shields.io/badge/Jupyter-F37626?style=for-the-badge&logo=jupyter&logoColor=white)
![Ollama](https://img.shields.io/badge/Ollama-000000?style=for-the-badge&logo=ollama&logoColor=white)

**Bezaleel** is a fully local, voice-controlled digital assistant built in Python. It combines traditional assistant features with smart local AI responses powered by Ollama (gemma2:2b).

### ✨ Key Features

- Real voice input using microphone (no wake word required)
- Loud and clear Text-to-Speech using gTTS + pydub
- Open popular websites and apps (YouTube, Spotify, JioSaavn, Twitter/X, Reddit, Gmail, WhatsApp, etc.)
- Music support — Play songs or open music platforms
- Local AI responses (gemma2:2b) for smart conversations
- News, Weather, Time & Date
- Jokes, Motivational Quotes
- Integrated Student Database (250 students across 5 sections)
- Clean interactive UI in JupyterLab

### 🎤 Example Commands

**AI Mode (Smart):**
- `smart explain AI in simple words`
- `smart give me a detailed explanation of how the internet works`

**Regular Commands:**
- `open spotify`
- `open jiosaavn`
- `play song perfect`
- `news`
- `total students`
- `average of section a`
- `highest marks`
- `how are you`

### Prerequisites

- Python 3.9+
- JupyterLab
- Ollama (with `gemma2:2b` model)
- Microphone
- FFmpeg (for louder voice)

**Install the model:**
```bash
ollama pull gemma2:2b
